// =============================================================================
// context/layer.vr — Context Layer Composition
// =============================================================================
// Grammar: layer_def = visibility 'layer' identifier layer_body
//          layer_body = '{' { provide_stmt } '}' | '=' layer_expr ';'
//          layer_expr = identifier { '+' identifier }
// Spec: docs/detailed/16-context-system.md
// =============================================================================

module layer;

// =============================================================================
// Layer Composition
// =============================================================================
//
// Layers are compile-time constructs that group `provide` statements for
// modular application assembly. The compiler resolves dependencies between
// layers and generates optimal initialization order.
//
// # Defining Layers
//
// ```verum
// layer DatabaseLayer {
//     provide ConnectionPool = ConnectionPool.new(Config.get_url());
//     provide QueryExecutor = QueryExecutor.new(ConnectionPool);
//     provide Migrations = Migrations.new(ConnectionPool);
// }
//
// layer LoggingLayer {
//     provide Logger = ConsoleLogger.new(Config.get_level());
//     provide Metrics = PrometheusMetrics.new(Config.get_endpoint());
// }
// ```
//
// # Composing Layers
//
// Layers compose via `+` for modular assembly:
//
// ```verum
// layer AppLayer = DatabaseLayer + LoggingLayer;
//
// fn main() {
//     provide AppLayer;  // Expands all provides in dependency order
//     run_server();
// }
// ```
//
// # Dependency Order
//
// Within a layer, provides are executed in declaration order.
// When composing, left-to-right: `A + B + C` → A's provides, then B's, then C's.
// The compiler detects circular dependencies at compile time.
//
// # Layer vs Context Group
//
// | Feature | Context Group | Layer |
// |---------|--------------|-------|
// | Defines | Required contexts | Provided values |
// | Syntax | `using WebCtx = [Database, Logger]` | `layer WebLayer { provide ... }` |
// | Usage | `fn f() using [WebCtx]` | `provide WebLayer;` |
// | Phase | Compile-time (requirement list) | Runtime (initialization) |
//
// Context groups declare WHAT you need. Layers declare HOW to provide it.
// They are complementary: use groups in function signatures, layers at boundaries.
